		<body>
			<!--<p>EHRI-DR-19420409-IT_EN</p>
      <p>Report of the envoy in Bratislava, Paolo Cortese, to the Italian Foreign Ministry.</p>
      <p>Cable No. 1290/287</p>
      <p>R. Legation of Italy</p>-->
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19420409-IT_01.jpg"/>
			<p>Addressed to Royal <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005042">Ministry of Foreign Affairs</orgName>,
				Rome.</p>
			<p>Bratislava, 9th April 1942, Year XX</p>
			<p/>
			<p>Re: Jewish question</p>
			<p>The coldness with which the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovakian</placeName> Catholic <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> has greeted the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">anti-Jewish action</term> of Minister of Interior
					<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000261">Mach</persName> is an indication of the mood of the
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovakian</placeName> Catholic <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-637" type="subject">population</term> which, particularly in the
				provinces, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-813" type="subject">feels no ill</term> will towards <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> and because of their meekness and
				religious upbringing disagrees with the violent methods used by the men carrying out the expulsion decrees. There have even been
				instances in which local authorities have not carried out or carried out only partially the ministerial orders. As many as three
				prefects have been deposed or recalled and subjected to an enquiry. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-767"
					type="subject">Church</term> authorities have also objected to the methods employed. It has been reported that the Minister of
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovakia</placeName> to the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3164670/state-of-the-vatican-city.html">Vatican</placeName> has been here, and there have been
				rumours about a note from the Secretariat of State to the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html"
					>Slovakian</placeName> Legation. There has indeed been such a step and the Chargé d’Affaires of the Holy See here has repeatedly
				seen the <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000413">Prime Minister</persName> and Minister for
				Foreign Affairs on this issue. Also, there have been critical voices against <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000261">Mach</persName> within the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> itself, coming from his colleagues
				of the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-471">Slovakian people’s party</orgName></p>
			<pb n="2" facs="EHRI-DR-19420409-IT_02.jpg"/>
			<p>Nonetheless, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">forced exodus</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> has continued and continues still. It is
				illegal, as no law authorizing it exists. There is – for now – only a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-542" type="subject">bill</term> approved a few days ago by
				the Council of Minister which has still to be submitted to Parliament. The full powers granted by Parliament to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> in 1940 to proceed against <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> cannot possibly apply to the issue of the
				exodus. As I have learned from Minister <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000261">Mach</persName>
				himself, of the 90,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> who were in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovakia</placeName> on 25th March last (in 1939 there were
				120,000, 30,000 of whom have voluntarily left the country after the establishment of the independent Slovak State), 13,000 have been
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deported</term> these past weeks to the
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3096472/katowice.html">Katowice</placeName> area and to the <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/units/de-002624-staatlakt-0_0-12-5">General Governorate</placeName> and those remaining will
				follow in the course of the next 6 months. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000261">Mach</persName>
				told me “The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> were dominating our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-918" type="subject">economy</term>”, and ended by saying that to remedy
				such a state of affairs, the time for half measures is over.</p>
			<p>When he was accused of having acted because forced to do so by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152"
					type="subject">Germans</term>, the <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000261">Minister of
					Interior</persName> declared to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject"
					>press</term>, as reported with Cable no. 1095/245 from <date when="1942-03-27">27th March</date>, that the expulsion of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> had been decided “spontaneously and with
				full persuasion”.</p>
			<p>I have been told by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">German</term> Minister here
				that his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> had not used any pressure
				but had simply made a suggestion that had been accepted.</p>
			<p>As far as I know, the <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000789">President of the Republic</persName>
				has done his utmost to mitigate the harshness of the methods employed for the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">exodus</term> and made use, despite a strong <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-954" type="subject">opposition</term> from the <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000413">Prime Minister</persName> himself, of the right to discriminate
				granted him by the “Jewish Code” in order to save a great many persons from expulsion. Clearly, if <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000789">President Tiso</persName> has not done more and has even
				prevented a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> controversy on the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish question</term> from breaking out (all that
				appeared in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term>, belatedly, were two
				critical articles in the Catholic <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1069" type="subject">newspapers</term>
				Slovak and Slovenska Pravda), this is due to the fact that he finds himself unable to oppose the will of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">Reich</term>, which has in <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000413">Tuka</persName> and in <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000261">Mach</persName>, <pb n="3" facs="EHRI-DR-19420409-IT_03.jpg"/>
				particularly in regard to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish
				question</term>, willing and convinced executors. It is also likely that Monsignor <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000789">Tiso</persName> judges that under any circumstances he can be
				more useful to his people in the presidential chair than elsewhere.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_dr_cortese_paolo">Cortese</persName></p>
			<p> </p>
